    "A spanning subgraph of a graph G is a subgraph containing all the vertices of G. Also, the undirected Cayley graph of a finite Abelian group G (with identity element 0) generated by set S ⊂ G is the graph with vertex set G and undirected edges (g, g + s) for all G g ∈ and all s ∈ S, s ≠ 0.",
